{"questionId":"12285","questionHtml":"<p>Find the set of values of <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"k\">\n  <mi>k</mi>\n</math></span> for which the system has a unique solution.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p class=\"questionCharChar\">System has a unique solution provided det&nbsp;<strong><em>A</em></strong> ≠&nbsp;0&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong> (R1)</strong></em></p>\n<p class=\"questionCharChar\"><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{k^2} + 2k - 1 \\ne 0\">\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mi>k</mi>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mn>2</mn>\n  <mi>k</mi>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mn>1</mn>\n  <mo>≠</mo>\n  <mn>0</mn>\n</math></span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>&nbsp;(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p class=\"questionCharChar\">Solving&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{k^2} + 2k - 1 \\ne 0\">\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mi>k</mi>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mn>2</mn>\n  <mi>k</mi>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mn>1</mn>\n  <mo>≠</mo>\n  <mn>0</mn>\n</math></span>&nbsp;or equivalent for <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"k\">\n  <mi>k</mi>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p class=\"questionCharChar\"><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"k \\in \\mathbb{R}\\,{\\text{\\ }}\\left\\{ { - 1 \\pm \\,\\sqrt 2 } \\right\\}\\,\\,\\left( {{\\text{accept}}\\,\\,k \\ne&nbsp; - 1 \\pm \\,\\sqrt 2 {\\text{,}}\\,\\,\\,k \\ne&nbsp; - 2.41{\\text{,}}\\,\\,0.414} \\right)\">\n  <mi>k</mi>\n  <mo>∈</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mi mathvariant=\"double-struck\">R</mi>\n  </mrow>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>\\&nbsp;</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>{</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mo>−</mo>\n      <mn>1</mn>\n      <mo>±</mo>\n      <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n      <msqrt>\n        <mn>2</mn>\n      </msqrt>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>}</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>accept</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n      <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n      <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n      <mi>k</mi>\n      <mo>≠</mo>\n      <mo>−</mo>\n      <mn>1</mn>\n      <mo>±</mo>\n      <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n      <msqrt>\n        <mn>2</mn>\n      </msqrt>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>,</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n      <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n      <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n      <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n      <mi>k</mi>\n      <mo>≠</mo>\n      <mo>−</mo>\n      <mn>2.41</mn>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>,</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n      <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n      <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n      <mn>0.414</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1&nbsp; N3</strong></em></p>\n<p class=\"questionCharChar\"><em><strong>[4 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"12285","referenceCode":"EXM.1.AHL.TZ0.54b","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Find the set of values of k for which the system has a unique solution.","paper":"1","level":"AHL","questionNumber":"b","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 4]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 1—Number and algebra","Topic 1—Number and algebra","AHL 1.14—Introduction to matrices"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}